Sentencas: Samaria doped ceria (SDC) electrolytes with theoretical Sm3+ doping concentrations (15, 20 and 25 mol%) were synthesized by electrospinning method and electrolyte performances were investigated for the first time in the literature.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: The samples were characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy-energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (SEM-EDS), thermogravimetric/differential thermal analysis (TG/DTA) and impedance analysis.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: It was determined that the Sm3+ contents of the samples were 17.4, 24 and 27.8 mol% instead of the theoretical values of 15%, 20% and 25% by using SEM-EDX analysis.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: XRD analysis confirmed that the doping of Sm3+ into Ce4+ was successful.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: The relative density of the samples was 95.8%, 81.4% and 76% for SDC-17, SDC-24, and SDC-28 samples respectively.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: The results showed that the sintering and the grain formation of the SDC nanofibers prepared by electrospinning method were difficult at particularly high samarium concentrations.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: It was found that the SDC-17 exhibited the highest ionic conductivity with the value of 0.0346 S cm(-1).
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method

Sentencas: Higher doping concentrations caused a decrease in ionic conductivity and an increase in activation energy.
Titulo: Structural, morphological and conductivity properties of samaria doped ceria (SmxCe1-xO2-x/2) electrolytes synthesized by electrospinning method
